------------------------------------------------------------------------
	METALLIC BONDS + BOND PROPERTIES
------------------------------------------------------------------------

	Metallic Bond: a group of positive Nuclei in a "sea" of mobile electrons

	Metalic Bonds occur between atoms of the same element.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
	The Electronegativity "Bonding Spectrum" 
------------------------------------------------------------------------

	A difference of zero between two elements in electronegativity
	means that it is either Metallic or nonpolar covalent. 

	A difference between zero and 1.7 between two elements in electronegativity 
	means that is is a covalent bond.

	a difference greater than 1.7 between two elements in electronegativity 
	means that it is an ionic bond.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Properties of Metallic Substances
------------------------------------------------------------------------

	- Good at conducting heat & electricity
	- High melting and boiling points
	- Malleable (can be deformed without breaking)
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Properties of Ionic Substances
------------------------------------------------------------------------

	- Good conductors of electricity when dissolved in water
	- Hard, crystalline (not malleable)
	- Very soluble in water

------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Properties of Covalent Substances
------------------------------------------------------------------------

	- Low melting and boiling points
	- Poor conductors of heat & electricity
	- Insoluble in water

------------------------------------------------------------------------
